In a statement on the 75th anniversary of the attack on Pearl Harbor, President Obama pays tribute to the American patriots who lost their lives in the attack. He highlights how their sacrifice inspired millions to defend liberty during a time of great peril. The President also expresses gratitude to the veterans and survivors of Pearl Harbor, acknowledging their bravery and the example they set. He emphasizes the enduring legacy of the Greatest Generation, who forged an international order, powered America's prosperity, and remind us of the importance of unity. President Obama reaffirms the ongoing commitment to secure and strengthen the nation, and expresses his anticipation for a visit to the USS Arizona Memorial with Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan, as a symbol of reconciliation and the enduring alliance between the two countries.